id: jf-ddd7
title: Fix sessions list output format and active playback fields
description: "GitHub issue #23 reports that sessions list bypasses the global output-format contract and omits active playback data. Reproduce against command wiring and formatters, route results through the shared output formatter, preserve machine-readable formats, and expose useful NowPlayingItem/PlayState details without leaking sensitive fields."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[4]: bug,github-23,output-format,sessions
created_at: "2026-07-16T16:49:04.255Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-16T17:00:04.524Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: "JSON, YAML, TOON, table, and default output follow the shared output contract.; Active playback fields are present when supplied and absent safely when not supplied.; Focused regression tests cover both formatting and playback projection."
goal: jf-mqpo
parent: jf-zifk
severity: high
environment: jellyfin-cli v2026.3.6 on main
repro_steps: Run sessions list with --output json or another global format; observe human-specific rendering and missing playback details.
expected_result: sessions list honors the requested global format and reports active playback fields consistently.
actual_result: output format is ignored and active playback context is omitted.
customer_impact: Agents cannot reliably parse session state and operators cannot see current playback context.
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
